WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:02.100
WHAT IS AN API HOW

2
00:00:01.580 --> 00:00:03.580
It Works

3
00:00:02.172 --> 00:00:04.249
An API, or Application Programming Interface,

4
00:00:03.949 --> 00:00:06.026
is a set of rules and

5
00:00:05.726 --> 00:00:07.802
protocols that allows different software applications

6
00:00:07.502 --> 00:00:09.502
to communicate with each other.

7
00:00:11.970 --> 00:00:13.970
HOW APIS WORK

8
00:00:12.858 --> 00:00:15.231
Client sends a request to the API

9
00:00:14.931 --> 00:00:16.931
API processes and forwards to

10
00:00:16.412 --> 00:00:18.412
the server

11
00:00:17.004 --> 00:00:19.004
Server performs the operation

12
00:00:18.188 --> 00:00:20.561
Response is delivered back to the client

13
00:00:20.261 --> 00:00:22.261
REST APIS

14
00:00:20.853 --> 00:00:22.930
REST APIs use standard HTTP methods:

15
00:00:22.630 --> 00:00:24.630
GET retrieves data

16
00:00:23.518 --> 00:00:25.518
POST creates new data

17
00:00:24.703 --> 00:00:26.703
PUT updates existing data

18
00:00:25.887 --> 00:00:27.887
DELETE removes data

19
00:00:26.776 --> 00:00:28.776
AUTHENTICATION

20
00:00:27.072 --> 00:00:29.148
When you use an API, you

21
00:00:28.848 --> 00:00:30.848
typically need:

22
00:00:29.441 --> 00:00:31.441
API key or access token

23
00:00:30.921 --> 00:00:32.921
Rate limiting to prevent abuse

24
00:00:32.402 --> 00:00:34.402
Proper permissions for resources

25
00:00:33.586 --> 00:00:35.586
DATA FORMATS

26
00:00:34.178 --> 00:00:36.255
APIs return data in various formats:

27
00:00:35.955 --> 00:00:46.289
JSON is the most popular

28
00:00:45.989 --> 00:00:47.989
XML is also common

29
00:00:47.173 --> 00:00:49.173
Uses key-value pairs

30
00:00:48.062 --> 00:00:50.062
REAL-WORLD EXAMPLES

31
00:00:48.654 --> 00:00:50.654
Google Maps API for maps

32
00:00:50.134 --> 00:00:52.134
Twitter API for social media

33
00:00:51.615 --> 00:00:53.615
Stripe for payments

34
00:00:52.503 --> 00:00:54.503
Weather APIs for forecasts

35
00:00:53.688 --> 00:00:55.688
APIs have revolutionized software development

36
00:00:55.168 --> 00:00:57.168
by enabling different applications to

37
00:00:56.649 --> 00:00:58.649
work together seamlessly.

